    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "On September 14, 2015, LIGO made history by detecting the first gravitational wave signal, known as **GW150914**, produced by the merger of two black holes. In this project we use a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to classify segments of LIGO data as either **signal** or **noise**.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Data\n",
    "\n",
    "We download the real LIGO strain data directly from the Gravitational Wave Open Science Center (GWOSC):"
